                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Zarath -- you miss the entire thought process of this post.
<br />

<br />
It takes 3-4 players other than an enchanter to control a high level charmed pet -- period.
<br />

<br />
Now go figure your dps - divide what the pet does by 4 or 5.
<br />

<br />
It is not the chanters that were overpowered -- it was that as chanters grew with the game -- we applied our varied and unusual talents to each situation -- with and with out the help of others.  And because our strategy defeated SOE's strategy to foil chanters -- they decided to just up and take away that ability.
<br />

<br />
I mean for 4-5 levels in the 50's and 60's - chanters could not charm anything in ldons -- either the spell was not a high enough level or groups that don't understand charm fighting don't let chanters charm.  Then we get to god level and its -- where is a chanter.  So now its chanters are overpowered -- in rare situations with a lot of help.(only 2 zones two are charmable in god)
<br />

<br />
I've seen Mage's tank ldons.  It is easy to see what a well equipped Mage can do.  And I luv grouping with a mage that knows how to play.
<br />

<br />
The point of this thread is to point out the extreme nature of the change to charm.  Chanters became chanters for the thrill of charm and the extra strategy needed to play one.  They did not become chanters to commit suicide everytime they charmed a pet nor play russian ruellete every time they mezzed a mob.
<br />

<br />
So if you find the topic extreme -- well good -- it was meant to be extreme to cry out to the utter distasteful way SOE is treating the chanter class.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
