                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Okay, I will take a shot at addressing the thread troll...(please feel free to skip to the parts beginning with Zarath's name)...
<br />

<br />
I tried charming when I got it at lvl 12...this was back in 2000, before twinking made any difference...I died a lot, and decided to stick to grouping a lot...you will note that this was when CC was king/queen...
<br />

<br />
Then along came the double-whammy of Velious/Luclin (plus a bad marriage, which added tremendously to my play time)...minimal grouping opportunities (except for AE groups, which had few openings on my server due to a variety of reasons which have no bearing on this topic), which lead to my finding things to do with my spell/skill set...I returned to charming...
<br />

<br />
Even without DC, a FG elite could clean house on the wurms in GD...good screenshots with DW whips taming those nasty beasts...made short work of farming my biles for the Coldain Shawl, too, as well as those for most of my guildies...
<br />

<br />
Charm kiting in Maidens Eye and Akheva Ruins was a ton of fun, as well as decent exp, and could be done solo/duo with a lot of time to chat while medding...got my treasured Shaded Hide Tunic during this time, too...
<br />

<br />
Then along came PoP...I ventured into PoN wondering how charm would work...hehe...the rest is history...
<br />

<br />
I dinged 65 first by weeks in my family guild due to the unlocking of Pacify/Lull, and finding the tunnels in PoJ...a hasted/DW drone reaps worm butt fast...still does...and filled in the gaps in exp zones until I got CoD plus my AD flag (this was well before HoH was a level limit zone for those latecomers to EQ)...
<br />

<br />
I made the most of the days of the 13 kill AA's in HoH, and had minimal issues with the nerfs which followed.  I missed the frantic moments of AE groups, but I had something to fill in my nights home from work.  
<br />

<br />
LDoN arrived, and I turned out to be the first one on my server to discover how to pac pull the places...taught several clerics the skill, as well as talking multiple bards into trying it out...I used to get paid to pull LDoN's--10k/run.  On the slow nights we would dual charm a run, and see how fast we could finish...
<br />

<br />
The fun in all of this was being a very non-uber player, to the point of people wondering how I did it with the crap gear I had at the time...I knew most of them from tradeskill contacts...I was the first 250 tailor on my server by 18+ months (/tips hat to second ex-wife for the time/need to do this) back in the days when a full set of Hazed Panther gear went for 150k (and 150k was serious plat back then).
<br />

<br />
Things stayed much the same through LoY...got my new spells...banked AA...was a guild leader...blah, blah, blah...
<br />

<br />
GoD comes out...yuck...yes, Tipt/Vexd were silly...I agreed that a fix was needed at the time...one is still needed in those zones...many valid ones (which would have worked, oddly enough) were proposed, with the snare/DW-immunity being the one I liked the most (i.e.:  charm overwrites snare/DW ability of mob), and I would have accepted the loss of hasting, though I liked having that option for burst dps.  Instead, things are left to fester...
<br />

<br />
OoW arrives...okay, "this is not a nerf"...right...I would have preferred honesty, especially after the guild summit...
<br />

<br />
Anyway, now you have to 2-box in a cleric for CH's to charm kill named mobs...great...the thing about charm pets is NOT so much the immense damage they put out, but the immense number of HP they bring to the table...it is sweet watching that CH land for 7500+ each and every time as the pet chews through the target...I have all of my 66-68 spells, and have been working 60-hour weeks at work while playing much less...easy to win the roll solo, huh?  I now have SoE to thank for giving me the incentive for leveling my cleric to 65 (and beyond, as I gain her core AA's, and collect runes for her 66+ spells---a fetish of mine is not leveling until I have the spells to do the job).  
<br />

<br />
Do we need ADC?  Not really, though I think if it had arrived with a dps reduction on the mob it would have been fine with a minimum of tweaking, while giving enchanters something to amuse themselves with...
<br />

<br />
Zarath...the root of our complaints is the OBVIOUS lack of thought, foresight, and concern for the future of the enchanter class which has been shown by SoE with the latest expansion.  The absolutely horrid CS is another point they need taking to task about.  This is deplorable in an industry which is becoming more competitive with each month, and reminds me of how the various phone companies acted when cable modems came out (most cable companies to this day offer much better CS than the local phone company, and installation is much faster with cable, though the last in due in part to federal regulation).  
<br />

<br />
Zarath, I ask you to point to the Mage spells which compare to Mayhem and Arcane Noose for lack of utility/insight into the class?
<br />

<br />
And, hey, how about that wonderful epic focus/clickie?  
<br />

<br />
How about the fact that no one has posted finding the start for the enchanter epic without finishing the first one, in spite of many searching and posting their confusion?  Not a single Dev has posted that they have CONFIRMED that it is live and working as intended--this in the face of their inadequate wording in our guidebook (which required an UNMENTIONED change to an item many of us had already aquired...a player had to spot it and post the change).
<br />

<br />
This is our bitch spot Zarath...we don't come to your home and make fun of your problems, please show us the same courtesy.  There is a wide range of ages represented in this class, as in all classes, so you have to expect some flames if you offer less than constructive criticism.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and DC can be dispelled...which hurts, as you aren't expecting that little thing to come back at you after buffing it to the gills, and giving it...wait for it...Mage gear...bad time to be AFK, if you follow my train of thought...LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...
<br />

<br />
Many of us are attempting to reach a reasonable consensus to take to the devs...the fact that no one seems to care what we think is just one more nail in the coffin for EQ...</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=570078" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Teyvan M'Crae</a>
<br />
Tier'Dal Coercer - Quellious - Scarlet
<br />

