                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">And actually, it IS about the DPS, because that's what got nerfed, and that's the reason it got nerfed. I had the ability to reclaim pets for mana, I had mod rods without timers and such...but they got too powerfull for the content and were nerfed into acceptable forms. That's what happened with Charm, Technically you still can charm so you didn't lose it, you just lost the damage. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
It's very simple.
<br />

<br />
Mod rods, reclaiming pets, and so on have NO risk associated with them. You sacrifice NOTHING to get the benefits of those items except some of your time and some of your mana.
<br />

<br />
Charm has risk associated with it. We can argue back and forth all day on how low the risk gets when you're doing it appropriately, but you have to admit that the risk is ALWAYS there. You can NEVER get it to zero.
<br />

<br />
Now, that said, YOU may feel that the DPS provided is in line with the extra risk your group accepts, and the extra attentiveness they've got to have. YOU may feel that charm in its current form is totally acceptable.
<br />

<br />
See all the other enchanters posting in this 7 page thread? They don't.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
