</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I never have said anything close to that, but if it makes you feel better to project your angst onto me, then have at it. I'll send you the bill for therapy.
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Omni wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
K, tell ya what.  For one raid/group, don't summon a pet and just nuke.  Make sure you wait 8 seconds before you nuke again.  Every hour and a half cast Shield of Maelin on yourself.  See how much fun that is.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
As a minor point, I actually raided back in the no pet days, so I know how bad it is. I actually raided in the rod whore days, so I know how bad being a 'bot is. I never said that Enchanters should not be fixed to have a fun and viable role- I simply am saying that DPS should not be it, especially the DPS levels available with Charm. But answer me, it sounds like all they changed was the damage charm did in OOW. If it is not about DPS, then how is it dead?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Nokei wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
Technically, you still can charm so you didn't lose, you just lost the REWARD side.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
 Well, the reward (high DPS, ability to kill "boss" type mobs, the soloability) was deemed too high and Sony adjusted it. Was it a bit harsh? Possibly. Could they figure out something better? Absolutely. Should you guys get some compensation? I think so, but not in damage. Do I think Charm should have been left alone? Absolutely not.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Honestly, I come here expecting a decent discussion, especially having heard the reputation of the Runes, only to find label throwing and bitterness easily matching that of the most jaded Mage. However, we have had years of practice, but welcome to the fold. I suggest you start targetting classes closer to you for your anger- Bards should work well. We get a kick out of poking the Beastlords. 
<br />

<br />
I really didn't come here to troll, I came here to give the counterpoint that you guys were missing, to give the rationale behind that of a DPS class and why we might be upset about it. But in true bitter player fashion (and I am a Mage, I know bitter) it's easier at first to label those that have opposing view points trolls. It helps to ease the pain.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
